det:"<h3>Early Life</h3>Born January 20, 1953 in Brooklyn, New York. Parents were Jewish working-class: father Seymour was a Parks Department groundskeeper, mother Pauline a school aide. Grew up in Sea Gate, Coney Island. Graduated Lafayette High School at 16 (skipped two grades). Attended Cooper Union and NYU's Courant Institute but left without a degree. In 1967, attended <a href='#interlochen'>Interlochen Center for the Arts</a> summer camp.\n\n<h3>Dalton School (1974-1976)</h3>Hired as math/physics teacher at <a href='#dalton-school'>Dalton School</a> at age 21 despite lacking credentials. Headmaster <a href='#donald-barr'>Donald Barr</a> had departed months earlier. Allegedly showed inappropriate behavior toward female students. Met <a href='#bear-stearns'>Bear Stearns</a> CEO Alan Greenberg through a parent. Dismissed in 1976 for 'poor performance.'\n\n<h3>Bear Stearns (1976-1981)</h3>Joined <a href='#bear-stearns'>Bear Stearns</a> as junior assistant, rose to options trader, became limited partner by 1980. Left in 1981 for 'Reg D violation.' Remained client until bank's 2008 collapse.\n\n<h3>Financial Consulting (1981-1987)</h3>Founded Intercontinental Assets Group. Worked recovering embezzled funds. Client of Saudi arms dealer <a href='#adnan-khashoggi'>Adnan Khashoggi</a> (Iran-Contra middleman). Met Steven Hoffenberg through John Mitchell. Possessed Austrian passport with false name showing Saudi residence. <a href='#alexander-acosta'>Acosta</a> later said he was told Epstein 'belonged to intelligence.'\n\n<h3>Towers Financial (1987-1993)</h3>Hired by Steven Hoffenberg as consultant. Company imploded as $450M Ponzi scheme in 1993. Hoffenberg claimed Epstein was 'intimately involved.' Epstein never charged.\n\n<h3>J. Epstein & Company (1988-2019)</h3>Founded <a href='#j-epstein-co'>J. Epstein & Co.</a> 1988. Primary known client: <a href='#leslie-wexner'>Leslie Wexner</a> (<a href='#victorias-secret'>Victoria's Secret</a>, L Brands). Met 1986, became financial advisor 1987. In 1991, Wexner granted full power of attorney. Received <a href='#9-east-71st'>9 East 71st St mansion</a> in 1998 for $20M. Used Victoria's Secret scout position to sexually manipulate young women.\n\nRevenue 1999-2018: $800M+ ($200M from Wexner, $170M from <a href='#leon-black'>Leon Black</a>). Moved to U.S. Virgin Islands for tax advantages (4% effective rate vs 38.5% top rate).\n\n<h3>Banking Relationships</h3><a href='#jpmorgan-chase'>JPMorgan</a> client 1998-2013 with 134 accounts. Close relationship with <a href='#jes-staley'>Jes Staley</a> (1,200+ emails). Bank dropped him 2013 after complaints. Moved to <a href='#deutsche-bank'>Deutsche Bank</a>. Treasury files show 4,725 wire transfers totaling $1.1B from one account; $1.9B+ across four banks.\n\n<h3>2005-2008 Investigation</h3>Palm Beach police began investigating 2005 after parent reported 14-year-old daughter recruited. FBI identified 36 victims. <a href='#alexander-acosta'>Alexander Acosta</a> negotiated controversial non-prosecution agreement with defense team (<a href='#alan-dershowitz'>Alan Dershowitz</a>, <a href='#kenneth-starr'>Kenneth Starr</a>). Pleaded to state charges, served 13 months with work release. Co-conspirators received immunity.\n\n<h3>2019 Arrest and Death</h3>Arrested July 6, 2019 at Teterboro returning from <a href='#avenue-foch'>Paris</a>. Charged with sex trafficking of minors. Found dead August 10, 2019 at <a href='#mcc-manhattan'>Metropolitan Correctional Center</a>. Medical examiner ruled suicide by hanging. Circumstances disputed: cameras not working, guards asleep, removed from suicide watch. Dr. Michael Baden (hired by brother Mark) said injuries more consistent with homicide. FBI released CCTV footage July 2025 but 2 minutes 53 seconds missing and video found modified.\n\n<h3>Aftermath</h3>Criminal charges dismissed August 29, 2019. <a href='#ghislaine-maxwell'>Ghislaine Maxwell</a> convicted December 2021, sentenced to 20 years. <a href='#jean-luc-brunel'>Jean-Luc Brunel</a> found dead in Paris cell February 2022. <a href='#epstein-victims-fund'>Epstein Victims' Compensation Fund</a> distributed $120M+ to 150+ victims. Properties sold: <a href='#9-east-71st'>Manhattan townhouse</a> $51M, <a href='#el-brillo-way'>Palm Beach</a> $18.5M (demolished), <a href='#little-st-james'>Little St. James</a> + <a href='#great-st-james'>Great St. James</a> $60M, <a href='#zorro-ranch'>Zorro Ranch</a> sold 2023.",
